{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632991","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632991"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:47:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:47:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17454"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17454","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17454"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10144"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70839"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10144","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10144"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17454"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56306"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5497"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23744"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23814"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70839","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70839"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare associated infections represent a significant burden on healthcare systems and lead to increased patient morbidity and mortality.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best defines a healthcare associated infection?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["An infection acquired from healthcare workers only","An infection occurring within 24 hours of admission","An infection present at hospital admission","An infection resistant to multiple antibiotics","An infection occurring as a result of healthcare"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Ehealthcare associated infection\u003C/strong\u003E is defined as an infection that occurs as a result of healthcare, and was not present or incubating at the time of admission. This time frame helps distinguish between community-acquired and healthcare associated infections.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAn infection present at hospital admission\u003C/strong\u003E represents a community-acquired infection that was already established before the patient entered the healthcare setting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAn infection acquired from healthcare workers only\u003C/strong\u003E is too narrow a definition, as healthcare associated infections can be transmitted through multiple routes including the environment, medical devices, and other patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAn infection occurring within 24 hours of admission\u003C/strong\u003E would likely represent a community-acquired infection as the timeframe is too short to attribute to healthcare exposure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAn infection resistant to multiple antibiotics\u003C/strong\u003E describes antimicrobial resistance patterns rather than the source of infection, as both community and healthcare associated infections can be resistant to antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding this definition is crucial for surveillance, prevention strategies, and appropriate management of healthcare associated infections.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Healthcare associated infections are defined as infections occurring more than 48 hours after hospital admission.","The most common types of healthcare associated infections are urinary tract infections, surgical site infections, bloodstream infections, and pneumonia.","Hand hygiene is the single most effective measure to prevent healthcare associated infections."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021.","Healthcare-associated infection program. Australian Commission on Safety and Quality in Healthcare. Available from: https://www.safetyandquality.gov.au/our-work/healthcare-associated-infection-program"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56306"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17454"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56306","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56306"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T14:29:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T14:30:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10144"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70839"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying 